## Hookify Architecture (Auto-Loaded)

Token efficiency and safety are enforced by hooks, not manual skills. Patterns auto-inject when relevant tools are called. **Stack-specific rules (e.g. the Supabase and n8n ones below) only fire if you actually use those tools — they cost nothing otherwise, and you can delete their rows if you never will.**

### SessionStart (1 hook)
| Hook | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `auto-rules` | 5 universal rules + hook reference tables |

### Lazy-Loading addContext (3 hooks)
| Hook | Triggers On | Injects |
|------|------------|---------|
| `supabase-auto-load` | Any Supabase MCP call | SQL patterns, anti-patterns, pre-query checklist |
| `n8n-auto-load` | Any n8n MCP call | Mode reference, 7 safety rules, STOP conditions |
| `task-context-injector` | Sub-agent spawn | Universal rules + CONTEXT_APPROVAL protocol |

### Warning Hooks (7 hooks)
| Hook | Triggers When | Fix |
|------|--------------|-----|
| `supabase-smart-query` | SQL missing LIMIT | Add LIMIT |
| `supabase-select-star` | SQL has `SELECT *` | Specify columns |
| `n8n-fetch-blocker` | `get_workflow` mode=full | Use mode=structure |
| `n8n-update-safety` | Any workflow update | Pre-update checklist |
| `n8n-executions-full` | `executions` mode=full | Use mode=error/summary |
| `github-file-contents` | Direct file fetch | Tree/glob first |
| `playwright-full-page` | fullPage=true | Viewport or snapshot |

### Block Hooks (2 hooks)
| Hook | What It Blocks |
|------|---------------|
| `mcp-server-guard` | Non-project MCP servers (configured by `/setup`) |
| `safe-bash-enforcer` | Catastrophic Bash patterns (`rm -rf /`, `eval`, fork bombs) |

### Safe-Bash (Privileged Workflow Enforcement)

Task scripts in `scripts/` enforce audit logging, metacharacter rejection, and deterministic hashing for privileged operations (n8n API calls, git commits). See `.claude/skills/safe-bash/SKILL.md`.

